description: a(n) is the number of nodes with depth of n in a binary tree defined as: root = 1 and a child (C) of a node (N) is such that C - primepi(C) = N, or A062298(C) = N. For a node with two children, the smaller child is assigned as the left child and the bigger one as the right child. Otherwise, the child is assigned as the left child.
